# Three.js Triangle Slider ("Spin")

## What It Is

The signature TREND slider breaks images into triangular faces and animates them along cubic bezier paths during transitions. One image disassembles while the next assembles, creating a dramatic particle-like effect.

## Canonical Module

The slider code lives at `src/lib/slider.js`. This is the single source of truth for the React app.

### Legacy Files (repo root)

- `slider.js` -- modernized ES module reference (complete, matches the React version)
- `slider22.js` -- **legacy/deprecated** IIFE version used by the original vanilla site. Do NOT port from this file. Do NOT use `var`, prototype-based classes, or IIFE patterns from it.

### Dependencies (CDN only)

- **Three.js r73** -- pinned; BAS requires the old `THREE.Geometry` API
- **BAS (Buffer Animation System)** -- `THREE.BAS.ModelBufferGeometry`, `THREE.BAS.BasicAnimationMaterial`
- **GSAP TweenMax 1.x** -- `TweenMax.to()` for tweening

Load via `<script>` tags in `index.html` `<head>`, NOT as npm packages:

```html
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/three.js/r73/three.min.js"></script>
<script src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/s.cdpn.io/175711/bas.js"></script>
<script src="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/gsap/1.18.0/TweenMax.min.js"></script>
```

Do NOT upgrade Three.js -- newer versions break BAS.

## Public API

### `createImageSlider({ container, images, width, height, delay })`

Creates one slider. Returns a dispose function (or `null` if deps missing).

### `createGallerySliders({ containers, images, staggerDelay })`

Creates multiple staggered sliders. Returns a dispose function.

## React Integration

NEVER use static `import` for `slider.js`. The file contains class definitions that reference `THREE` at module scope (`class Slide extends THREE.Mesh`). A static import causes the class to evaluate before CDN scripts load, crashing the entire app.

Always use **dynamic `import()`** inside `useEffect`:

```jsx
import { useRef, useEffect } from 'react'
import { useIsMobile } from '../hooks/useIsMobile'

export const HeroSlider = ({ images, width, height, delay = 0 }) => {
  const containerRef = useRef(null)
  const isMobile = useIsMobile()

  useEffect(() => {
    if (isMobile || !containerRef.current || !images.length) return
    if (typeof THREE === 'undefined') return

    let disposed = false
    const disposers = []

    import('../lib/slider.js').then(({ createImageSlider }) => {
      if (disposed) return
      const d = createImageSlider({
        container: containerRef.current,
        images, width, height, delay
      })
      if (d) disposers.push(d)
    })

    return () => {
      disposed = true
      disposers.forEach(d => d())
    }
  }, [isMobile, images, width, height, delay])

  if (isMobile) return null

  return <div ref={containerRef} className="hero-slider" />
}
```

### Key Rules

- NEVER static-import `slider.js` -- always use dynamic `import()` inside `useEffect`
- CDN scripts load asynchronously -- poll for `THREE`/`TweenMax` with `setTimeout` retry instead of checking once and giving up
- Always return the dispose function from `useEffect` -- it cleans up WebGL resources
- Skip initialization on mobile -- render a CSS fallback instead
- Use `useRef` for containers, never query the DOM
- Hero images load instantly via static `<img>` previews; the slider animation starts later on top

## Slider Placements

| Location | Width | Height | Delay |
|---|---|---|---|
| Hero left | 70 | 105 | 0 |
| Hero right | 70 | 105 | 500ms |
| Gallery (x4) | 120 | 160 | i * 200ms |

## Mobile Fallback

On mobile (`useIsMobile()` true), render a CSS crossfade instead of the Three.js slider. The slider module also returns `null` when `THREE` is unavailable.

## Image Loading

- Slider images are provided by the React app, typically using Vite-imported assets from `src/data/imageImports.js`
- In the standard setup, images are local files under `src/assets/images/**` bundled by Vite (no external CDN dependency)
- After each transition, the current image reference is copied (no re-download) and only the next image is fetched
